President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Gregory Slavonic to be an Assistant Secretary of the Navy, Manpower and Reserve Affairs. Slavonic has a 34-year career in the U.S. Navy and has served in various leadership positions. He has also written books on leadership development and co-authored a book on American Olympian Jim Thorpe. In addition, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts, including members of the American Battle Monuments Commission, the Board of Trustees of the James Madison Memorial Fellowship Foundation, and the President's Commission on White House Fellowships.